MAJOR BLUE tracked from behind the leaders while in the two path around the turn, chased while aiming between foes in upper stretch, but faded. BRIGADIER GENERAL bumped with an outer rival at the start, stalked two wide, bid for the lead along with an outer foe turning for home, but got outkicked while shifting to the five path entering the lane, and weakened. THE RIDER OF KING OTTOMAN CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF PETULANTE FOR INTEREFENCE IN THE STRETCH; BUT THE OBJECTION WAS DISALLOWED BY THE STEWARDS.

ANDTHEWINNERIS bumped with an inner rival at the start, trailed in the three path around the first turn, moved out of last in the four to five paths around the far turn before fanning to the seven path entering the lane, stayed on while shifting ground inwardly in midstretch, and leveled off in the final furlong without reaching contention. MENDELSSOHNS MARCH bounced off an outer rival at the start, shifted out and put that foe to tight quarters a sixteenth of a mild late, laid off of the pace two wide and between horses, and failed to factor. ANGLOPHILE raced off of the pace three wide and between horses, and failed to factor among foes in the lane. SCOOBIE QUANDO lacked speed while hung four wide, came under coaxing around the far turn, spun into the lane in the six path and between horses, got outkicked while being subtly put to tight quarters at the furlong pole, checked mildly in the aftermath, and lacked a rally thereafter. OTAGO got briefly keen among foes entering the first turn, tracked two wide and between horses around that bend, required urging to sustain position around the far turn, then gave way while shifting to the five path in upper stretch. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Old Forester Bourbon Turf Classic S. - Grade1 CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 11 1 1/8M Turf CR: 120. Stakes Purse 1000000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UP TO THE MARK lunged out and bumped a rival leaving the gates, settled off of the pace in the three path, inched closer in the three to four paths around the far turn before fanning out at the quarter pole, loomed large in the seven path entering the lane, offered a good kick to drive past the leaders in upper stretch, drew clear entering the final furlong, and was put to hand with victory secured in the final sixteenth. HONG KONG HARRY (IRE) was slow out of the gates, settled towards the rear in the two path, fanned to the six path entering the lane, rallied in the seven path while chasing the clearing leader's charge in midstretch, and gained place at the sixteenth pole. SPOOKY CHANNEL bumped with an inner rival at the start, trailed around both turns, spun into the lane in the five path, shifted out to the eight path at the three sixteenths pole, offered a late rally outside of foes in the final furlong, and reached show at the wire. OCEAN ATLANTIQUE tracked along the inside, vacated the rail around the far turn before turning for home two wide and between horses, shifted out to the five path while hanging on his left lead and failing to quicken among foes in upper stretch, but changed leads inside the three sixteenths, kept on with a steady grind between horses to gain show in the final sixteenth, but got nailed at the wire. SANTIN got a bit warm pre-race, bumped with an outer rival at the start, pressed the leader from the three path around the first turn, vied in the two path around the far turn, led while shifting back to the three path entering the lane, but offered little resistance to UP TO THE MARK's challenge leaving upper stretch, and faded. WOLFIE'S DYNAGHOST stalked along the inside, vacated the rail to take aim in the four path and between horses at the three sixteenths pole, but lacked the needed rally to produce a bid. EARLS ROCK (IRE) took a bump from an inner rival at the start, tracked from the three path, chased outside of the leading pair around the far turn, floated to the five, then six, paths while between horses in upper stretch, gave way on his left lead soon after, changed over in midstretch, but continued to weaken. BYE BYE MELVIN set the pace inside of a pressing foe, but was headed by that one nearing the lane, and weakened in upper stretch. PER RULING #23-0059 FROM THE KENTUCKY RACING COMMISSION, HONG KONG HARRY (IRE) WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM 2nd TO UNPLACED DUE TO A POSITIVE TEST.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Kentucky Derby presented by Woodford Reserve - Grade1 CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 12 1 1/4M Dirt CR: 106. Stakes Purse 3000000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS, WITH AN ENTRY FEE OF $25,000 EACH AND A STARTING FEE OF $25,000 EACH.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAGE broke a step slow but avoided trouble between horses by doing so, shifted inwardly and across DISARM's heels after a furlong, settled far back in the two to four path and between horses around the first turn, tucked back to the two path approaching the far turn, smoothly tipped five wide leaving the three furlong pole, rallied outside of rivals turning for home before tipping to the seven path entering the lane, sustained his charge to bear down on the leader nearing midstretch, bid at the furlong pole, edged an advantage soon after and held well. TWO PHIL'S received light contact from an inner rival at the start, stalked behind the embattled leader two wide and from between horses, produced an early bid inside of the KINGSBARNS as that one gained a brief lead between calls with three furlongs to go, edged clear while tipping to the two path entering the lane, but met MAGE's outer challenge nearing midstretch, got headed by that one at the furlong grounds, fought on doggedly thereafter but was bested and saved place. ANGEL OF EMPIRE tucked in to save ground, moved into position on the backstretch, moved with the winner on the second turn, worked his way to the outside, came seven wide, quickened once straightened and was getting to the leaders late. DISARM broke a bit inwardly at the start, laid off of the pace along the inside, pursued two wide around the far turn, tipped to the four, then five, path while among foes in upper stretch, bumped with an inner RAISE CAIN approaching midstretch and ran on well to gain a minor share. HIT SHOW tracked the top flight from the two to three path around the far turn, responded to rousing to range up outside of the leading trio entering the far turn, gradually progressed around that bend to spin into the lane in the five path while within striking range but flattened out between horses. DERMA SOTOGAKE (JPN) broke inward, brushed the gate soundly and was away slow, settled between runners down the stretch and into the first turn, worked his way forward in tight quarters, moved to the outside on the second turn while continuing the advance, came six wide and toiled on through the drive. TAPIT TRICE was slow into stride under moderate urging in the opening stages, trailed in the two to three path around the first turn, moved out of last entering the backstretch, attempted to launch a rally by shifting from the three path to the five path approaching the five sixteenths pole, but squarely bumped MANDARIN HERO (JPN) in the process, fanned to the eight path entering the lane and failed to sustain a rally while leveling off. RAISE CAIN settled along the inside, took closer order down the backstretch, kept on through the second turn, got through into the stretch, lacked room and tacked outward nearing the furlong marker, was bumped and checked when the tiring KINGSBARNS drifted about, altered out further but lacked a response thereafter. ROCKET CAN settled between rivals while not far off of the inside, mounted an early move after the opening half for position, churned on in traffic through the second turn and into the lane within striking distance but flattened in the final furlong and faded. CONFIDENCE GAME stalked just behind the leaders along the inside, tapped on the brakes briefly when too close to those rivals in the latter half of the first turn, pursued comfortably along the rail down the backstretch, got subtly shuffled behind a stopping VERIFYING entering the far turn before surpassing outside of that foe soon after, tipped back to the inside turning for home, but only managed to chase in upper stretch and faded through the final furlong. SUN THUNDER hopped at the start and was away a step slow, was unhurried off of the inside, came under a ride into the second turn, moved up between foe, angled in entering the stretch and improved belatedly. MANDARIN HERO (JPN) settled four wide in mid pack, was bumped hard and forced further out midway through the second turn when TAPIT TRICE came out and came up empty thereafter. REINCARNATE broke a bit outwardly towards open space as his outer counterpart left a step slow, prompted the top pair three wide around the first turn, sustained pressing position under coaxing entering the far turn but weakened between horses turning for home. KINGSBARNS dueled for the lead two wide and between horses entering the first turn, sparred down the backstretch, inherited an advantage from his inner faltering counterpart entering the far turn, but only led briefly before getting headed by an inner bidding TWO PHIL'S leaving the three furlong pole, gave way in the three path entering the lane, lightly brushed with an inner rival before bumping with an outer foe inside the three sixteenths pole, steadied in the aftermath and dropped back. KING RUSSELL was hung wide throughout and lacked a response. VERIFYING brushed an outer rival upon leaving the gates, dueled for the lead inside of a pair of pressers around the first turn, clung to an advantage down the backstretch, but weakened at the seven sixteenths pole, and wilted along the rail around the far turn. JACE'S ROAD was forwardly placed four wide, but stopped before going six furlongs. CYCLONE MISCHIEF was unhurried while widest and was never a factor. OAKS DERBY PICK 6 WINNING NUMBERS 1-14-5-1/2/7-2/4/5-8/9/10/15/19/20.
